<subSubSection id="C37713E8AD52FFF99563FA5E93FBD187" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD24063AD52FFF99563FA5E90F7D159" blockId="10.[98,1066,1486,1686]" lastBlockId="11.[106,1074,1209,1478]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD52FFF89563FA5E9299D1A9" box="[98,190,1486,1512]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD52FFF895CEFA5E93B6D1A9" authority="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb, 2020" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[207,401,1486,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limerai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD52FFF895CEFA5E93B6D1A9" box="[207,401,1486,1512]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Purenleon limerai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD52FFF8949AFA5E93F9D1A9" bold="true" box="[411,478,1486,1512]" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A210AAD52FFF8949AFA5E93F9D1A9" box="[411,478,1486,1512]" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
clearly fits into the tibialis species group. It has all the characteristics of the group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC3D92AD52FFF8975BFA619144D24A" author="Miller, R. B. &amp; Stange, L. A." box="[602,867,1521,1547]" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref8829" refString="Miller, R. B. &amp; Stange, L. A. (2014) A revision of the genus Purenleon Stange (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae: Nemoleontini). Insecta Mundi 384: 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="2014">Miller &amp; Stange (2014)</bibRefCitation>
: mid tibia greatly swollen, much broader than foretibia and basitarsus of hind leg about twice as long as greatest diameter. Unfortunately, the female is unknown and the presence of the small lobes on the posterior margin of sternite VII, another major characteristic of the group, still needs confirmation. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD52FFF89474F9EC901BD2D7" authority="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb, 2020" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[373,572,1660,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limeirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD52FFF89474F9EC901BD2D7" box="[373,572,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Purenleon limeirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD52FFF89743F9EC90A6D2D7" bold="true" box="[578,641,1660,1686]" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A210AAD52FFF89743F9EC90A6D2D7" box="[578,641,1660,1686]" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seems to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD52FFF896C9F9ED960ED2D7" authorityName="Miller &amp; Stange" authorityYear="2014" box="[968,1065,1660,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD52FFF896C9F9ED960ED2D7" box="[968,1065,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">P. tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(only known from 
<collectingCountry id="F37A00F3AD53FFF99449FB299399D095" box="[328,446,1209,1236]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">Colombia</collectingCountry>
), their mostly yellow body color pattern is unique for these two species within the genus, but they can be clearly separated based on the shape of the male terminalia, as mentioned in the key below.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1210EBAD53FFF9956BFC6B9046D00D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786717" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3786717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3786717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="73" startId="11.[106,139,1019,1041]" targetBox="[306,873,132,993]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8BD24063AD53FFF9956BFC6B9046D00D" blockId="11.[106,1074,1019,1100]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD53FFF9956BFC6B928ED051" bold="true" box="[106,169,1019,1041]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">Fig. 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD53FFF995B4FC6B937CD051" authority="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb, 2020" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[181,347,1019,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limeirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD53FFF995B4FC6B937CD051" box="[181,347,1019,1040]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">Purenleon limeirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD53FFF99462FC6B93BDD051" bold="true" box="[355,410,1019,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A210AAD53FFF99462FC6B93BDD051" box="[355,410,1019,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male: a) terminalia, lateral view; b) genitalia, lateral view; c) genitalia, posteroventral view; d) genitalia, posterodorsal view. E = ectoproct; G = gonarcus; M = mediuncus; P = paramere; S = sternite; T = tergite. Scale bar = 0.5mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD24063AD53FFF99586FAB193FBD187" blockId="11.[106,1074,1209,1478]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">
Although the species description is based on only one specimen, it is justified by its unique characteristics (especially in the male terminalia), which clearly distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D3BE0AD53FFF9956BFAF69315D1C1" authority="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb, 2020" authorityName="Machadoa &amp; Tavaresb" authorityYear="2020" box="[106,306,1382,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Purenleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limeirai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD53FFF9956BFAF69315D1C1" box="[106,306,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">Purenleon limeirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9199C71AD53FFF99438FAF6935DD1C1" bold="true" box="[313,378,1382,1408]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A210AAD53FFF99438FAF6935DD1C1" box="[313,378,1382,1408]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from the other 3 species in the tibialis species group. Furthermore, the difficult access to the 
<typeStatus id="54D6FEC1AD53FFF994DDFA1A902BD1E5" box="[476,524,1418,1444]" pageId="11" pageNumber="73">type</typeStatus>
locality hinders further opportunities to collect more specimens in a near future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
